subSubSection.paragraph:
The ornament is densely tuberculate. The tubercles are tightly-spaced and arranged into rows in locations close to the plate’s margin; these rows are parallel to the plate’s lateral edges in a small specimen (NUFV 796) and perpendicular to the cranial and lateral margins in large specimens (NUFV 874, 898; 
Fig. 4
). In positions along the lateral margin of the largest known posterior median dorsal plate (NUFV 898; 
Fig. 4
), the tubercles are fused together to 
form ridges
.

